name: They Might Be Giants - Tour Poster 2013
description:
They Might Be Giants Tour Poster 2013

What can you say about TMBG? A truly original, brilliant and nutty band that I have long loved and respected. From their educational albums for kids to the excellent idea of 'dial-a-song', they are out there on their own (seriously, check out their wikipedia page if you don't believe me) , so I was very pleased to get to make a tour poster for them. 

Featuring a cigar smoking parrot that looks like he's been around the block, but by God does he have some stories to tell. 

Limited edition signed and numbered poster
Edition of 195
4 colour screenprint
59.5cm x 42cm

Poster for two sold out shows by Josh Ritter at London's Village Underground. Josh wanted a design that conveyed some sort of duality, or that had some sort of double take maybe. And as if that weren't enough, each t-shirt comes with one of four sets of temporary tattoo sheets based on the design to trick your friends and wow the ladies/gents of your dreams.

Inspired by the bands use of Constructivist imagery on previous releases i decided to try and re-imagine constructivist poster design via the streets of a moonlit Glasgow. I guess to put it another way, what if Rodchenko had come from Scotland?
